[code]public boolean posNeg(int a, int b, boolean negative) {
  if (negative) {
   return (a < 0 && b < 0);
  } else {
   return ((a < 0 && b > 0 || a > 0 && b < 0));
  }
}[/code]

It was really difficult, I looked at the arrows and the last return, because it was just way too difficult.

[code]public boolean icyHot(int temp1, int temp2) {
   //Written as icyHot int temp1, so you return true if one > 0 < 100;
   if ((temp1 < 0 && temp2 > 100) || (temp1 > 100 && temp2 < 0)) {
	return true;
